Package civitas.celestis.math.vector

Class Decimal2

java.lang.Object
civitas.celestis.util.group.Pair<BigDecimal>
civitas.celestis.math.vector.Decimal2
All Implemented Interfaces:
BigVector<BigDecimal,Decimal2>, DecimalVector<Decimal2>, Vector<BigDecimal,Decimal2>, Collectable<BigDecimal>, Listable<BigDecimal>, Group<BigDecimal>, Groupable<BigDecimal>, Tuple<BigDecimal>, Transformable<BigDecimal>, Serializable, Iterable<BigDecimal>
public class Decimal2 extends Pair<BigDecimal> implements DecimalVector<Decimal2>
An AB-notated two-dimensional vector which uses BigDecimal to represent its components.

    • equals

      public boolean equals(@Nullable Object obj)
      Checks for equality between this group and the provided object obj.

      Unless explicitly stated otherwise in an overridden comment, this will check is the other object is also a group, and the composition of the two groups are equal.

      This requires that the two groups use the same method of indexing. (e.g. Tuple vs. Grid; the former uses one-dimensional indexing whereas the second uses two-dimensional indexing. Thus, a tuple and a grid cannot be equal)

      Specified by:
      equals in interface Group<BigDecimal>
      Specified by:
      equals in interface Vector<BigDecimal,Decimal2>
      Overrides:
      equals in class Pair<BigDecimal>
      Parameters:
      obj - The object to compare to
      Returns:
      true if the object is considered equal by the conventions mentioned above
